
Overview of noun gleaming

The noun gleaming has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (1) gleam, gleaming, glimmer -- (a flash of light (especially reflected light))
2. (1) gleam, gleaming, glow, lambency -- (an appearance of reflected light)

Overview of verb gleam

The verb gleam has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (3) glitter, glisten, glint, gleam, shine -- (be shiny, as if wet; "His eyes were glistening")
2. (3) gleam, glimmer -- (shine brightly, like a star or a light)
3. (1) gleam -- (appear briefly; "A terrible thought gleamed in her mind")

Overview of adj gleaming

The adj gleaming has 1 sense (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) agleam, gleaming, nitid -- (bright with a steady but subdued shining; "from the plane we saw the city below agleam with lights"; "the gleaming brass on the altar"; "Nereids beneath the nitid moon")
